# Capstone: Admin Dashboard

A data-dense admin app is the ultimate test of *systematic* Tailwind: the app shell, container-query
layouts, accessible tables and forms, dark mode, and performance under real complexity.

<ProjectBrief
	title="Build a production admin dashboard"
	time="3–5 hours"
	goal="Build a multi-view admin dashboard on your design system and app shell: overview with stat cards and a chart, a data table with sorting/filtering, a detail drawer, and a settings form — accessible, themed, tested, and CI-guarded."
	requirements={[
		'Reuse the Module 9 app shell (sticky header, collapsible sidebar, mobile drawer)',
		'Overview: stat cards (semantic positive/negative deltas) + a chart area',
		'An accessible, sortable, filterable data table (th scope, caption, keyboard)',
		'A detail drawer/modal with focus trapping and Escape-to-close',
		'A settings form with validation, accessible errors, and disabled/loading states',
		'Light/dark, contrast-safe; container-query responsive layout',
		'At least 3 component tests + a CI workflow (lint/check/test/build)'
	]}
	stretch={[
		'Lazy-load the charting library on mount (perf budget)',
		'Add command-palette navigation (headless + Tailwind)',
		'Add an empty-state and skeleton-loading pass for every view'
	]}
/>

